── SECTION 4: 5h SLIDING WINDOWS BY DOMINANT MODEL ────────────────────

  A window is labeled "4.6" or "4.7" if >50% of calls use that model.
  Only considers windows starting from Apr 2 (fair comparison span).

  Dominant | Windows | Mean Util | p50 Util | p90 Util | p99 Util | Max Util | >80% | >100%
  ---------|---------|-----------|----------|----------|----------|----------|------|------
       4.6 |     963 |     45.8% |    15.0% |   132.1% |   574.6% |   630.6% |  173 |   147
       4.7 |     174 |     19.8% |     7.1% |    59.1% |   104.1% |   110.8% |    7 |     7

  Mean utilization 4.7 / 4.6 ratio: 0.43x
  p90  utilization 4.7 / 4.6 ratio: 0.45x

── KEY FINDINGS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  1. Per-call token multipliers (4.7 vs 4.6):
       input      0.09x   (advisory: 1.0–1.35x tokenizer)
       output     2.61x   (advisory: adaptive thinking heavier)
       cache_read 1.20x   (advisory: cache metering anomaly ~7x reported)

  2. Iter-call share: 4.6 57.9%, 4.7 78.8%
     Iter-output share: 4.6 98.5%, 4.7 99.9%
     Δ 1.4 pp — small.

  3. Sample sizes: 4.6 32299 calls, 4.7 2615 calls.
     CAVEAT: early-window 4.7 data. Workload mix may not match 4.6 baseline.
